From: m5-linux project
Subject: [PATCH 3/N] chickens: Add M4 Pro/Max and M5 CPU feature stubs

Uses features_m4 as the starting point for all new chips — same as how
T8140 (A18 Pro) was added. The "XXX figure out what features are actually
available on M4" comment already exists in m1n1; M5 inherits the same
uncertainty. Feature flags will be refined during bring-up.

--- a/src/chickens.c
+++ b/src/chickens.c
@@ ... (after T8140 Tahiti entries) ...
+    /* M4 Pro (T6040) */
+    {MIDR_PART_T6040_ECORE, "M4 Pro Brava (E core)", NULL, &features_m4},
+    {MIDR_PART_T6040_PCORE, "M4 Pro Brava (P core)", NULL, &features_m4},
+    /* M4 Max (T6041) */
+    {MIDR_PART_T6041_ECORE, "M4 Max Brava (E core)", NULL, &features_m4},
+    {MIDR_PART_T6041_PCORE, "M4 Max Brava (P core)", NULL, &features_m4},
+    /* M5 base (T8142) — codename Hidra */
+    /* XXX: features_m5 struct needed once M5 CPU errata are known */
+    {MIDR_PART_T8142_ECORE, "M5 Hidra (E core)",    NULL, &features_m4},
+    {MIDR_PART_T8142_PCORE, "M5 Hidra (P core)",    NULL, &features_m4},
+    /* M5 Pro (T6050) — codename Sotra */
+    {MIDR_PART_T6050_ECORE, "M5 Pro Sotra (E core)", NULL, &features_m4},
+    {MIDR_PART_T6050_PCORE, "M5 Pro Sotra (P core)", NULL, &features_m4},
+    /* M5 Max (T6051) */
+    {MIDR_PART_T6051_ECORE, "M5 Max (E core)",       NULL, &features_m4},
+    {MIDR_PART_T6051_PCORE, "M5 Max (P core)",       NULL, &features_m4},

NOTE: "Brava" is the rumored M4 Pro/Max CPU core codename based on the
arithmetic pattern (Avalanche/Blizzard → Everest/Sawtooth → Brava?).
Verify against ADT `compatible` strings in the IPSW cpu nodes.
